The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Saturday, August 21, 2004  Business Briefs																								 New Delhi, Aug. 20: Key infrastructure industries posted a growth of 7 per cent in July against 2.8 per cent a year ago. Electricity generation was up 13.9 per cent and cement 8 per cent. Coal output was up 6.6 per cent, while crude oil production was almost stagnant. Finished steel and petroleum refinery products grew 3 per cent.																								 New Delhi, Aug. 20: A parliamentary committee today pulled up the finance ministry for the fall in the tax-GDP ratio to 9.2 per cent in 2003-04 from 10.1 per cent in 1990-91. This happened due to reduction in tax rates and non-recovery of Rs 68,477 crore in arrears.																								 New Delhi, Aug. 20: The government is examining the provisions of the lapsed Convergence Bill 2001 and will be ready with a fresh one by early next year, said I amp;B minister S. Jaipal Reddy.																								 New Delhi, Aug. 20: The demand for gold in the country increased 20 per cent in rupee terms and demand for jewellery was up 17 per cent during January-June 2004.																								 New Delhi, Aug. 20: Sebi is ironing out differences on regulatory overlap and harmonising various provisions of the listing agreement and Companies Act with the department of company affairs.
